node.text:
In 2010, psychologist Daniel Kahneman and economist Angus Deaton undertook research to discover if more money meant more happiness, it turns out  beyond a certain point ($75k/year in America), it doesn't...⁣
⁣
Now, of course $75k year is still above average and may seem like a huge sum to those not from a wealthy nation.⁣
⁣
However, it does make it clear that more money is not the answer to increasing happiness.⁣
⁣
More money can bring more comforts, more security and less stress, all amazing things - this is why we pursue more money.⁣
⁣
But, before you think about trying to get more money, you need to get your life in order by making the most of what you already have.⁣
⁣
With a sound mind, a healthy body, clear objectives, good social ties and uplifting hobbies, you can be happy even on a modest income.⁣
⁣
And from that point, any extra money you make can be deployed to make you happier. You just can't make an unhappy person happy with money alone. You can make a happy person even happier with more money though.⁣
⁣
What do you think?⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

You're the only person with your exact goals.⁣

So, why compare yourself to others?⁣

node.text:
⚠️ Before you swipe away: I agree with you, courses are a ripoff...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
They usually have a few videos with some vague information you could have got for free on YouTube, maybe a few good pointers here and there but mostly they just hype you up for a short while and then leave you disappointed.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
That's why I wrote an ebook instead.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The Instagram Bible contains over 100 pages of educational content that goes through the exact procedure I took in building my page from nothing to over 500,000 followers - generating over $10k a month - in a little over a year and a half.⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Money is something you only respect when you've experienced it's scarcity...⁣
⁣
Whilst most of us don't need to be told that, we're not the children of billionaires, we can learn something from this about money.⁣
⁣
Once we've achieved basic comforts and financial security, having more money won't make us happier, however the pursuit of it might.⁣
⁣
If you pick a business model, investing strategy, career that you enjoy. You will find increasing your wealth to be much more enjoyable than actually having that extra money.⁣
⁣
If you're struggling right now, you might not believe this logic but once you've reached a place where you're financially secure, you'll see it for yourself.⁣
⁣
This is why you should pick ways of making money that are meaningful and enjoyable to you. If you pursue money in a way you despise doing, money will simply make you unhappy.⁣
⁣
Love the process, not the reward.⁣
⁣
